<reference id="enum_camerastabilizationmode">
    <title><ph keyref="CAMERA_STABILIZATION_MODE"/></title>
    <shortdesc id="short"><ph id="shortdesc">Camera stabilization modes.</ph></shortdesc>
    <refbody>
        <section id="detailed_desc">
            <dl outputclass="since">
                <dlentry props="native">
                    <dt>Since</dt>
                    <dd>v4.3.1</dd>
                </dlentry>
            </dl>
            <p>The camera stabilization effect increases in the order of 1 &lt; 2 &lt; 3, and the latency will also increase accordingly.</p>
        </section>
        <section id="parameters">
            <title>Enumerator</title>
            <parml>
                <plentry>
                    <pt><ph keyref="CAMERA_STABILIZATION_MODE_OFF"/></pt>
                    <pd>-1: (Default) Camera stabilization mode off.</pd>
                </plentry>
                <plentry>
                    <pt><ph keyref="CAMERA_STABILIZATION_MODE_AUTO"/></pt>
                    <pd>0: Automatic camera stabilization. The system automatically selects a stabilization mode based on the status of the camera. However, the latency is relatively high in this mode, so it is recommended not to use this enumeration.</pd>
                </plentry>
                <plentry>
                    <pt><ph keyref="CAMERA_STABILIZATION_MODE_LEVEL_1"/></pt>
                    <pd>1: (Recommended) Level 1 camera stabilization.</pd>
                </plentry>
                <plentry>
                    <pt><ph keyref="CAMERA_STABILIZATION_MODE_LEVEL_2"/></pt>
                    <pd>2: Level 2 camera stabilization.</pd>
                </plentry>
                <plentry>
                    <pt><ph keyref="CAMERA_STABILIZATION_MODE_LEVEL_3"/></pt>
                    <pd>3: Level 3 camera stabilization.</pd>
                </plentry>
            </parml>
        </section></refbody>
</reference>
